TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Single Machine Problem with a Quadratic Cost Function of Completion Times
AU  - Szwarc, Wlodzimierz
AU  - Posner, Marc E.
AU  - Liu, John J.
Y1  - 1988/12/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.34.12.1480
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.34.12.1480
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1480
EP  - 1488
VL  - 34
IS  - 12
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper examines a single machine sequencing problem with a quadratic cost function of completion times. A new type of precedence relation is constructed that determines the ordering between adjacent jobs. Each pair of jobs has a critical start time, after which the precedence relation changes direction. These relations are incorporated into a solution procedure that solved 191 out of 200 test problems with job sizes ranging from 15 to 100 without using enumeration methods. Although 9 problems were not solved directly by the procedure, even these were reduced to 10 much smaller problems (of the job sizes 3 and 4) which could easily be solved by inspection.
AB  - This paper examines a single machine sequencing problem with a quadratic cost function of completion times. A new type of precedence relation is constructed that determines the ordering between adjacent jobs. Each pair of jobs has a critical start time, after which the precedence relation changes direction. These relations are incorporated into a solution procedure that solved 191 out of 200 test problems with job sizes ranging from 15 to 100 without using enumeration methods. Although 9 problems were not solved directly by the procedure, even these were reduced to 10 much smaller problems (of the job sizes 3 and 4) which could easily be solved by inspection.
